##### MF6: PRODUCT ENERGY-ANGLE DISTRIBUTIONS                     8431 1451
                                                                  8431 1451
In MF6 we store all secondary energy, angle, and energy-angle     8431 1451
distributions, as well as all residual and discrete + continuum   8431 1451
photon production cross sections for channels other than capture  8431 1451
(MT102) and reactions to discrete levels (MT51,etc.).             8431 1451
All data are generated with TALYS.                                8431 1451
                                                                  8431 1451
- MT5      : (n,anything) yields and energy-angle distributions   8431 1451
                                                                  8431 1451
MT5 contains, in this order,                                      8431 1451
For neutrons up to alpha particles and photons:                   8431 1451
- the production yields per particle for the whole energy range   8431 1451
- the secondary energy-angle distributions per particles which are8431 1451
  not represented by explicit MT numbers. On a secondary energy   8431 1451
  grid the relative emission spectra are given together with the  8431 1451
  parameters for the Kalbach systematics for angular              8431 1451
  distributions. Inelastic scattering cross sections for discrete 8431 1451
  states have been broadened and added to the continuum spectra.  8431 1451
For each residual product:                                        8431 1451
- the production yields for the whole energy range.               8431 1451
- the recoil                                                      8431 1451
These distributions can be multiplied with MF3/MT5 to get         8431 1451
the production cross sections and (double-)differential cross     8431 1451
sections.                                                         8431 1451
                                                                  8431 1451
- MT16     : (n,2n) energy-angle distr. and photon production     8431 1451
                                                                  8431 1451
First, for each type of outgoing particle, the (trivial) integer  8431 1451
particle yields are given. Next, on a sufficiently dense incident 8431 1451
energy grid the secondary energy-angle distributions are          8431 1451
specified by means of the relative emission spectra and the       8431 1451
parameters for the Kalbach systematics for angular distributions. 8431 1451
Next, the photon yield is tabulated as a function of incident     8431 1451
energy. For each incident energy, the photon production is given  8431 1451
for all discrete gamma lines present in the final nucleus. A      8431 1451
continuum photon distribution is added to this. We assume         8431 1451
isotropy for all produced gamma rays.                             8431 1451
                                                                  8431 1451
For the following MT-numbers, the same procedure as for MT16 is   8431 1451
followed:                                                         8431 1451
                                                                  8431 1451
